**                                                                   **
**                 ***** RULES FOR TTT *****                         **
**                                                                   **
***********************************************************************
***********************************************************************


  TTT IS A THREE-DIMENSIONAL TIC-TAC-TOE GAME.
  THE BOARD CONSISTS OF 64 SQUARES, ARRANGED ON 4 LEVELS OF 16 (4X4)
      SQUARES EACH:

    ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___
    ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___
    ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___
    ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___

      LEVEL 1          LEVEL 2          LEVEL 3          LEVEL 4


   YOU HAVE TO IMAGINE THAT LEVEL 1 IS DIRECTLY ABOVE LEVEL 2, WHICH
   IS DIRECTLY ABOVE LEVEL 3, WHICH IS DIRECTLY ABOVE LEVEL 4.LOOKING
   SIDEWAYS AT THE STACK, YOU WOULD SEE:

    ___.___.___.___  LEVEL 1
    ___.___.___.___  LEVEL 2
    ___.___.___.___  LEVEL 3
    ___.___.___.___  LEVEL 4

   THE PURPOSE OF THE GAME IS TO GET 4 IN A ROW. THE ROW CAN BE
   HORIZONTAL, VERTICAL, OR DIAGONAL.

   TO ENTER YOUR MOVE, TYPE IN A 3-DIGIT NUMBER. THE FIRST NUMBER IS
   THE LEVEL, THE SECOND IS THE ROW, AND THE THIRD IS THE COLUMN. YOU
   CAN SEE THE LEVEL FROM THE ABOVE BOARD DRAWINGS. ROW AND COLUMN
   WITHIN A LEVEL ARE:
                             COLUMNS
                           1   2   3   4
                   R  1   ___|___|___|___
                   O  2   ___|___|___|___
                   W  3   ___|___|___|___
                   S  4   ___|___|___|___


   SOME MOVE EXAMPLES ARE SHOWN BELOW. THE @ IS LOCATED AT 111 (LEVEL 1,
   ROW 1, COLUMN 1), THE # IS AT 234 (LEVEL 2, ROW 3, COLUMN 4), THE 0
   IS AT 413 (LEVEL 4, ROW 1, COLUMN 3), AND THE X IS AT 342 (LEVEL 3,
   ROW 4, COLUMN 2).

    _@_|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___  ___|___|_0_|___
    ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___
    ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|_#_  ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___
    ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___  ___|_X_|___|___  ___|___|___|___

   AFTER EACH MOVE, THE COMPUTER WILL SHOW YOU THE GAME BOARD WITH YOUR
   NEW MOVE AND HIS FOLLOWING MOVE. YOUR CURRENT MOVE SHOWS UP AS A #,
   AND ALL YOUR PREVIOUS MOVES ARE SHOWN BY X'S. THE COMPUTER'S CURRENT
   MOVE IS AN @, AND PREVIOUS COMPUTER MOVES ARE SHOWN BY 0'S.

   TO LET THE COMPUTER MOVE FIRST, ENTER 000 FOR YOUR FIRST MOVE.

   TO END A GAME (GIVE UP) AND START A NEW ONE, ENTER -1.

   TO STOP PLAYING TIC-TAC-TOE, ENTER 999.

   TO RE-DISPLAY THE GAME BOARD, ENTER 666. NOTE THAT THERE WILL BE NO
   "CURRENT" MOVES WHEN YOU DO THIS, ONLY 0'S AND X'S. IT OFTEN HELPS
   TO DO THIS TO BETTER SEE WHERE ALL THE MOVES ARE AFTER YOU'VE NOTED
   THE CURRENT MOVES. CLEAR THE SCREEN AND ENTER 666 TO BE SURE THE
   BOARD DOESN'T GO OFF THE BOTTOM.


   HERE ARE SOME WINNING POSITIONS:
     (A) HORIZONTAL

    _X_|_X_|_X_|_X_  ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___  ___|___|___|___
