***********************************************************************
**                                                                   **
**                 ***** RULES FOR TARGET  *****                     **
**                                                                   **
***********************************************************************
***********************************************************************

  THIS GAME SIMULATES THE FIRING OF AN ARTILLERY GUN. YOU ARE THE
  OFFICER IN CHARGE, WHO DIRECTS THE GUN CREW BY GIVING THE ELEVATION
  TO BE USED. THIS IS SPECIFIED IN DEGREES, FROM 0 TO 90 DEGREES.
  THE ELEVATION ANGLE CAN BE GIVEN AS A DECIMAL NUMBER WITH UP TO
  2 DECIMAL PLACES, OR AS A WHOLE NUMBER. EXAMPLES OF CORRECT
  ELEVATIONS ARE: 10  45.0  39.75  89.6 ETC. THE MAXIMUM RANGE OF
  YOUR GUN IS 46,500 YARDS, WHICH OCCURS WHEN THE ELEVATION IS 45
  DEGREES. ANY ELEVATION LESS THAN 45 OR GREATER THAN 45 WILL DECREASE
  THE RANGE OF THE GUN.

  WHEN THE GAME BEGINS, YOU ARE TOLD THE DISTANCE TO THE TARGET, AND
  ASKED FOR THE ELEVATION TO BE USED. THE GUN IS ASSUMED TO BE
  POINTED IN THE RIGHT DIRECTION.

  FOR THE FIRST GAME, THE ENEMY DOES NOT SHOOT BACK, AND YOU HAVE THE
  TIME TO EXPERIMENT AROUND A LOT IN TRYING TO HIT THE TARGET. A HIT
  WITHIN 100 YARDS OF THE TARGET DESTROYS IT. AFTER THE FIRST GAME,
  THE ENEMY FIRES BACK AFTER EACH SHOT YOU MAKE. ENEMY FIRE GETS
  CLOSER WITH EACH SHOT, UNTIL YOU HAVE BEEN DESTROYED, SO YOU HAVE
  TO BE MORE ACCURATE TO SURVIVE.

  AFTER YOU DESTROY THE TARGET, THE COMPUTER WILL ASK IF YOU WISH TO
  CHARGE OR RETREAT. IF YOU REPLY "CHARGE", ANOTHER TARGET WILL BE
  PRESENTED, AND THE GAME CONTINUES. IF YOU REPLY "RETREAT", THE GAME
  IS ENDED.

                H
                            .
             H     H   .         .
                   .                .
           H    .    H                .
              .                         .
         H  .          H                  .
          .         L      L                .
       H.   L            H        L           .
      .                   H            L        .

   THE ABOVE PICTURE SHOWS WHAT HAPPENS AS THE ANGLE OF ELEVATION IS
   INCREASED AND DECREASED. THE ..... LINE SHOWS 45 DEGREES (MAXIMUM
   RANGE). THE HHHH LINE SHOWS WHAT HAPPENS WITH ELEVATIONS GREATER
   THAN 45 DEGREES, AND THE LLLL LINE WITH ELEVATIONS LOWER THAN 45
   DEGREES.





***********************************************************************
***********************************************************************
**                                                                   **
**                 ***** RULES FOR COFFEE *****                      **
**                                                                   **
***********************************************************************
***********************************************************************

  THE COMPUTER WILL PICK A NUMBER BETWEEN 0000 AND 9999 RANDOMLY.
  THE IDEA IS TO GUESS THE EXACT NUMBER. AFTER EACH GUESS, THE COMPUTER
  WILL TELL YOU IF THE GUESS WAS TOO HIGH OR TOO LOW. YOU MUST ENTER
  A 4-DIGIT NUMBER HIGHER THAN THE PREVIOUS LOWEST GUESS, AND LOWER
  THAN THE PREVIOUS HIGHEST GUESS. WINNER BUYS THE COFFEE.




